cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NA, cs.SP 

The paper deals with the identification and performance analysis of a general formulation of independent vector analysis (IVA), which is a popular technique in machine learning and signal processing. The paper discusses the identification conditions for linear, nonlinear, and sample-to-sample dependencies, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Signal Processing). The paper also provides performance bounds in terms of the Cramer-Rao lower bound, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SP (Signal Processing). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NA, and cs.SP.
